CauseDesc: No tool gripped and gripper missing from storage position
SolutionDesc: Verify if a gripper is physically gripped by the robot flange and the gripper is physically present at the storage position

CauseDesc: Tool storage sensor (H1-BG18/H1-BG19/H1-BG20) gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Adjust the sensor position, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and robot controller

CauseDesc: Tool gripped sensor (K6-BG6) gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Verify if the gripper is gripped completely at the robot flange and adjust the sensor position, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and robot controller

CauseDesc: This parameter is not transmitted by the PLC
This program is not existing on the robot controller
SolutionDesc: Verify the program names on the robot controller

CauseDesc: The front cover is missing on the pallet to start the robot
SolutionDesc: Check the cause for the missing front cover and place a front cover on the pallet

CauseDesc: The sensor (G1-BG50/G1-BG51) at the stopper position gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Adjust the sensor position/settings, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and PLC

CauseDesc: The front cover is missing at the vision field
SolutionDesc: Check the cause for the missing front cover and place a front cover on the vision field

CauseDesc: Too much external light or image out of focus at the vision field
SolutionDesc: Adjust the camera aperture and focus to suite the external light conditions

CauseDesc: The LED light bed at vision field is turned off
SolutionDesc: Turn on the LED light bed / verify all the cables and connections between the light bed and power supply

CauseDesc: The assembly position is occupied by a workpiece, hence blocking the robot from starting
SolutionDesc: Remove the workpiece from the assembly position

CauseDesc: The sensor (H1-BG10/H1-BG11/H1-BG12) at the assembly position gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Adjust the sensor position/settings, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and robot controller

CauseDesc: The front cover is missing at the assembly position
SolutionDesc: Check the cause for the missing front cover and place a front cover at the assembly position

CauseDesc: The sensor (H1-BG10) at the assembly position gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Adjust the sensor position/settings, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and robot controller

CauseDesc: The front cover is placed upside down at the assembly position
SolutionDesc: Verify the front cover orientation and place the pocket side facing up

CauseDesc: The sensor (H1-BG11) at the assembly position gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Adjust the sensor position/settings, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and robot controller

CauseDesc: The front cover is placed with the hole on the left side
SolutionDesc: Verify the front cover orientation and place the hole side on the right side

CauseDesc: The sensor (H1-BG12) at the assembly position gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Adjust the sensor position/settings, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and robot controller

CauseDesc: No air supply to the clamp unit at assembly position
SolutionDesc: Check the air connection to the clamp unit

CauseDesc: The actuator (H1-MB9) output is not turned on
SolutionDesc: Turn the output signal to true, if it's still not working verify all the cables and the connection between the sensor and the robot controller

CauseDesc: The sensor (H1-BG9) at the assembly position gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Adjust the sensor position/settings, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and robot controller

CauseDesc: This parameter is not transmitted by the PLC
The range of the PCB pallet no. is 0 > PCB Number > 10
The number of fuses in all the fuse magazines are less than 2
SolutionDesc: Check the number of fuses and fill the fuse magazines

CauseDesc: The sensor (H1-BG14/H1-BG15/H1-BG16) of the fuse magazine gives false signal
SolutionDesc: Adjust the sensor position/settings, if it's still not working verify all the cables and connection between the sensor and robot controller

CauseDesc: Failure on the main power supply
data connection on the ceiling turns down

SolutionDesc: Reset of the machine and new start

CauseDesc: Failure during the adjusting of CNC milling
Throttle valve is too wide turned up
Mechanical blocking of the gripper arm

SolutionDesc: Reset of the machine and new start

CauseDesc: No enable of the application quality control, application is in default mode
Pneumatic cylinder is moving too slow
Part cannot be found in MES4 buffer.

ErrorNo: - Buffer is not correctly booked in MES4.

SolutionNo: Book MES4 buffer correctly. Refil the part in storage.
